&lt;p&gt;As a Consultant with the Strategy and Communications team, your role will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research and analysis&lt;/strong&gt; – conduct desktop research and analysis to contextualise market, geopolitical and/ or business trends and understand how it may impact clients’ businesses. Other areas of strategic support may include industry and peer benchmarking and preparation of reports and insights for senior leadership and Board level executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Horizon scanning&lt;/strong&gt; – keep abreast of current trends, news, and developments in the public domain, which include proactive media monitoring, and evaluate impact on clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;– Build understanding and lists of stakeholder targets to support client account work, which may include but not limited to journalists, influencers, analysts and investors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content development&lt;/strong&gt; – contribute to the creation of compelling and impactful content for various communications channels including traditional media, digital, and social media. Collaborate with colleagues to develop client ready documents to support messaging executive materials and campaign support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account support&lt;/strong&gt; – assist the wider account team in managing client relationship by providing support during client meetings, developing and maintaining client communication materials, taking notes, updating project trackers, and helping to ensure all client needs are met in a timely and satisfactory manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supporting new business development&lt;/strong&gt; - supporting senior members of the team with new business proposals e.g. conducting research and developing insights to support the proposal building process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, you will be expected to:&lt;/p&gt;
