&lt;li&gt;Lead forensic data acquisition, preservation, processing and analysis activities across a broad range of electronic data sources, ensuring defensibility and adherence to industry best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex forensic technology and eDiscovery engagements across the full EDRM lifecycle, from data preservation and collection through processing, review, production and expert support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Devising, reviewing and updating standard operating procedures on an ongoing basis, and providing training to members of the team as needed. Drive innovation through improvements to methodologies, automation and technology adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively planning workload and tasks across the team, managing multiple active concurrent engagements, often with regulatory or court-imposed deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the trusted advisor to clients on forensic technology, and eDiscovery strategy, managing senior client stakeholders and legal counsel throughout complex investigations and disputes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide quality &amp;amp; risk management and project oversight across multiple data workstreams or projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the strategic growth of the regional and global Forensic Technology practice by leading and assisting in marketing, business development and proposition development activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play an active role in the capability development of the Forensic Technology team and coaching of junior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;National and international travel may be required on an infrequent basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
